3	> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
4	
5	**Goal:** A read-only Copilot-style center modal listing custom agents, skills, instructions, hooks, and MCP servers (global + per-project, both providers), plus a Projects section that shows/hides projects in the rail.
6	
7	**Architecture:** Provider modules gain read-only `customizations` scanners (all path knowledge stays in `server/lib/providers/`); one new REST route merges them; the client renders a modal with a left nav and list/detail panes. Project visibility is a `hidden: string[]` array on the existing persisted config, filtered client-side in the rail. Every item is file-path addressed — the seam v2 editing builds on (see `.claude/docs/customizations-roadmap.md`).
8	
9	**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Fastify, Next.js 15 + SCSS modules, vitest, `marked` (already installed) for markdown.
10	
11	**Spec:** `docs/todo/2026-07-10-customizations-browser.md` — read it before starting.
12	
13	## Global Constraints
14	
15	- Hard rule 3: no `~/.claude` / `~/.codex` path or agent binary name outside `server/lib/providers/`.
16	- Hard rule 6 (codex): schema-discover against the real `~/.codex` before building codex scanners — never guess fields.
17	- Style rule: text styled ONLY via `t-*` mixins from `styles/typography.scss`; component `.module.scss` = layout/spacing/state only; shared visuals compose `components/ui/` primitives. `npm run lint:styles` must stay green.
18	- No writes to any agent store in v1 — scanners are read-only.
19	- Tests are hermetic: injected deps, fixture dirs under `os.tmpdir()`, never the real home dir.
20	- The tree is shared with other agents' uncommitted work: commit each task **by pathspec** (`git commit -- <files>`), never `git add -A`.
21	- Full gates after every task: `npx vitest run <new test file>` during the loop, `npm test && npx tsc --noEmit` before each commit.
